# nl-rag distilled facts — domain: 1884-columbus-buckeyes-season
# one declarative sentence per line; load with:  neuron --db app.db import pack.facts --scope knowledge
[src:1884-columbus-buckeyes-season/1883-columbus-buckeyes-season] The **1883 Columbus Buckeyes** finished with a 32–65 record, sixth place in the American Association.
[src:1884-columbus-buckeyes-season/1883-columbus-buckeyes-season] This was the first season in the major leagues for the team.
[src:1884-columbus-buckeyes-season/1884-baltimore-monumentals-season] The **1884 Baltimore Monumentals** finished with a 58–47 record in the Union Association, finishing in fourth place.
[src:1884-columbus-buckeyes-season/1884-baltimore-monumentals-season] This was the only season this version of the team existed, and indeed the only season the Union Association existed.
[src:1884-columbus-buckeyes-season/1884-boston-beaneaters-season] The **1884 Boston Beaneaters season** was the 14th season of the franchise.
[src:1884-columbus-buckeyes-season/1884-boston-reds-season] The **1884 Boston Reds** finished with a 58–51 record in the Union Association, finishing in fifth place (fourth among teams that played a full schedule).
[src:1884-columbus-buckeyes-season/1884-boston-reds-season] This was the only season the team existed, and indeed the only season the Union Association existed.
[src:1884-columbus-buckeyes-season/1884-brooklyn-atlantics-season] The **1884 Brooklyn Atlantics season** was a season in American baseball.
[src:1884-columbus-buckeyes-season/1884-brooklyn-atlantics-season] It was the first season in the American Association for the team, and they finished the year in ninth place.
[src:1884-columbus-buckeyes-season/1884-brooklyn-atlantics-season] The Brooklyn baseball team had played as the **Brooklyn Grays** in the Interstate Association in 1883, where they won the championship.
[src:1884-columbus-buckeyes-season/1884-brooklyn-atlantics-season] In 1884, Charles Byrne moved the team into the American Association, renaming them the Atlantics in tribute to the old National Association Brooklyn Atlantics team.
[src:1884-columbus-buckeyes-season/1884-buffalo-bisons-season] The **1884 Buffalo Bisons** finished the season with a 64–47 record, good for third place in the National League.
[src:1884-columbus-buckeyes-season/1884-columbus-buckeyes-season] The **1884 Columbus Buckeyes** finished with a 69–39 record, second place in the American Association.
[src:1884-columbus-buckeyes-season/1884-columbus-buckeyes-season] The team folded at the conclusion of the season.
